caption.p:
Phylogenetic tree based on protein sequences of selected FIPs. 24 amino acid sequences (

    Supplementary Table S1
   ) were analyzed. The evolutionary relationship between FIPs were inferred using the Neighbor-Joining method, and Jones-Taylor-Thornton (JTT) model was used to compute evolutionary distances. The numbers at the nodes indicate bootstrap support values (%). The scale bar represents 0.5 substitutions per site.
